 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Leadership Sourcer, Specialized Technology Facebook 622 reviews Remote Remote Facebook 622 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. The Specialized Technology Recruiting Team at Facebook supports specialized technical hiring across unique hardware initiatives and innovative technologies. These organizations are responsible for developing and building the software and hardware platforms that power Facebook, its Infrastructure, and its family of apps today (including Data Center, Core Systems Engineering, Foundation, Enterprise, Network Engineering, Production Engineering, Connectivity, Privacy and Security teams) and the platforms of the future (Augmented and Virtual Reality (AR/VR) and Artificial Intelligence (AI)).As a member of the Specialized Technology Recruiting Team, youâ€™ll work with hiring managers and Recruiters to develop creative strategies to find the best talent globally. We conceive practical and creative ways to identify leading talent and invest a lot of time activating passive candidates through a highly engaged approach. Weâ€™re passionate about delivering an awesome candidate experience from the initial reachout and first conversation a candidate has with us which more often than not starts with a member of our recruiting team. 
Help to define, design and implement leadership recruiting programs and search engagements for a variety of technical leadership roles, including understanding and mapping the talent landscape, internal calibration and referrals, and matching those data points with the external talent supply 
Partner with leadership, recruiters and hiring managers to develop a detailed profiles of target candidates with data-driven advice on the range of logical possibilities 
Skillfully support weighing the anticipated and immediate challenges of the targeted role, company/group strategic objectives, and corresponding opportunities to productively explore more diverse perspectives and tradeoffs 
Foster trust-based relationships with candidates, gaining a close understanding of their requirements and concerns 
Support an exemplary candidate experience at every stage of the process 
Strategize different ways to build talent pipelines and execute on tactical research, referral generation, events and sourcing campaigns 
Screen resumes and assess candidates to determine appropriate next steps 
Regularly track pipeline activity to share with internal stakeholders 
Proactively recommend and drive process improvements that impact candidate identification and engagement 
Capture and maintain accurate market, client and candidate information on our knowledge management systems so as to both facilitate the search process and our overarching Market Intelligence initiatives 
Leverage search and problem-solving expertise on a variety of Facebook Global Recruiting initiatives 
Become a contributing member of the Recruitment Leadership team that effectively embodies and promotes the culture and values of Facebook, and lead the team to do the same 
5 or more years of experience with recruiting 
2+ years of experience in technical and/or leadership recruiting 
Experience market mapping and engaging senior-level candidates 
Experience partnering with hiring teams, recruiters and clients, including senior management 
Experience developing talent market insights and data to influence leadership and cross-functional team decisions 
Demonstrated track record of building working relationships with leaders and cross-functional partner 
7+ years of experience in a combination of retained executive search research and large corporate technology identifying and developing software engineering leadership candidate interest 
Knowledge, comfort and versatility working on complex or technical sourcing topics 
Fearless and resilient, highly driven to be successful, an interest in technology and continuous learning 
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started. 
Facebook is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based upon race, religion, color, national origin, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender, gender identity, gender expression, transgender status, sexual stereotypes, age, status as a protected veteran, status as an individual with a disability, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state and local law. Facebook is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities in our recruiting process. If you need any assistance or accommodations due to a disability, please let us know at accommodations-ext@fb.com. 
